HB 625 Original 2026 Regular Session Jordan
Abstract: Establishes the insurance requirements for peer-to-peer car sharing programs.
Present law provides that a peer-to-peer car sharing program has an insurable interest in a
shared vehicle during the car sharing period, specifies that nothing in the Section creates
liability for the program to maintain certain coverage, and authorizes the program to own
and maintain motor vehicle liability insurance policies covering specified liabilities and
losses.
Proposed law revises present law to remove language stating that the Section does not create
liability for a peer-to-peer car sharing program to maintain required coverage.
Proposed law requires a peer-to-peer car sharing program to own and maintain as the named
insured a policy of insurance written by an insurer admitted or approved in this state that
provides coverage for physical damage for collision and comprehensive losses to the shared
vehicle during the car sharing period.
Proposed law further provides that the required policy applies when the shared vehicle
owner’s policy excludes or does not provide such coverage, and authorizes the required
